text.section:
The following persons shall be exempt from the prelicensing course of study requirements for specific lines of authority of KRS 304.9-105(1)(e)1.:
Persons holding a Chartered Life Underwriter (CLU) designation for a life line of authority;
Persons holding a Chartered Property and Casualty Underwriter (CPCU) designation for property, personal lines, and casualty lines of authority;
Persons holding a Certified Insurance Counselor (CIC) designation for life, health, property, personal lines, and casualty lines of authority;
Persons holding a designation as a Certified Employee Benefit Specialist (CEBS), Chartered Financial Consultant (ChFC), Certified Financial Planner (CFP), Fellow of the Life Management Institute (FLMI), or Life Underwriter Training Council Fellow (LUTCF) for a life line of authority;
Persons holding a designation as a Registered Health Underwriter (RHU), Certified Employee Benefit Specialist (CEBS), Registered Employee Benefit Consultant (REBC), or Health Insurance Advisor (HIA) for a health line of authority;
Persons holding a designation as an Accredited Advisor in Insurance (AAI) or Associate in Risk Management (ARM) for property, personal lines, and casualty lines of authority; and
Persons holding an insurance degree from an accredited college or university for all lines of authority.
